VIENNA -- At least eight people have been confirmed killed and 30 others injured as two avalanches roared through a ski resort in Austria's western state of Triol on Tuesday evening, the Austrian news media reported.
Avalanche developments: The death toll has risen to 16; 29 missing.
Witnesses said there were no casualties in the attack, in which a passenger on a motor scooter sprayed bullets.
More than 60 people have died in avalanches in Europe this year.
